Transcription.Text: Then I went over to the lamp, bent to blow it out. From behind me in the doorway I heard the slither of footsteps. I had forgotten Seona. Standing in the doorway, her nose wrinkled in disgust at the smell in the room, was the woman Jeronimo had called Elsa.
